reviewText:
You know you need to re-evaluate your life when a pigeon dating sim makes you cry ;_;

My housemates think I'm actually crazy and I think I am in love with a fictional bird.

Seriously though, wtf just happened? Story gets pretty dark...I really did not see that coming. Loved it!

A dating Sim with birds? Pah, that's ridiculous!... is what you are probably thinking. And you are right, but that is not the whole truth; beneath its satirical surface, Hatoful Boyfriend hides a gripping story that turns it into a very solid Visual Novel.

+ The silly humour makes this VN accessible even to those who are not into Japanese culture, making it excellent (and affordable) for those seeking to dip into the genre;
+ While short, the main routes are solid and varied, ranging from tear-jerkers to plain WTF, with some hilarity in between (try Okosan's route first of all!)
+ The hidden" (and arguably "canon") route presents a very interesting darker tale;
+ The OST and visuals are not mind-blowing

helpfulPercent:
 I do think some routes could've been fleshed out a little more;
- The translation has some typos and English oddities.

VERDICT: If you think that this game is just a gimmick

